        <name>XV_hscaler_ConfigTable</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Configuration table for <ref refid="struct_x_v__hscaler" kindref="compound">XV_hscaler</ref> instances. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This table contains the configuration parameters for each instance of the <ref refid="struct_x_v__hscaler" kindref="compound">XV_hscaler</ref> hardware core. Each entry describes the hardware properties and capabilities of a specific <ref refid="struct_x_v__hscaler" kindref="compound">XV_hscaler</ref> device.</para><para>Fields:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>compatible: Device compatibility string.</para></listitem><listitem><para>reg: Base address of the hardware instance.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,samples-per-clock: Number of samples processed per clock cycle.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,num-video-components: Number of video components supported.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,max-cols: Maximum number of columns (horizontal resolution).</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,max-rows: Maximum number of rows (vertical resolution).</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,max-data-width: Maximum data width per component.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,phase-shift: Phase shift value for scaling.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,scale-mode: Supported scaling mode.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,taps: Number of filter taps.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,enable-422: Enable support for YUV 4:2:2 format.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,enable-420: Enable support for YUV 4:2:0 format.</para></listitem><listitem><para>xlnx,enable-csc: Enable color space conversion.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para><para>The table is placed in the &quot;.drvcfg_sec&quot; section for driver configuration. </para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
