        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function looks up the configuration for a given device using the specified base address, and then initializes the <ref refid="struct_x_v__hscaler" kindref="compound">XV_hscaler</ref> instance with the found configuration. If the configuration cannot be found, the function sets the instance as not ready and returns an error code.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_v__hscaler" kindref="compound">XV_hscaler</ref> instance to be initialized. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Base address of the device to initialize.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if initialization was successful.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_DEVICE_NOT_FOUND if the device configuration could not be found.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The caller must ensure that the InstancePtr is not NULL.</para></listitem><listitem><para>This function must be called before using the <ref refid="struct_x_v__hscaler" kindref="compound">XV_hscaler</ref> instance. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
